upiInitDescriptionEntry.name: upiInitDescriptionEntry
upiInitDescriptionEntry.description: the entry associated with each UPInit process

upidInitIpAddr.name: upidInitIpAddr
upidInitIpAddr.description: the ip address of the host running UPInit

upidInitVersion.name: upidInitVersion
upidInitVersion.description: the version of the UP system

upidInitProcessType.name: upidInitProcessType
upidInitProcessType.description: one of these : UPLInit, UPAdmInit, UPAppsInit

upidInitHostName.name: upidInitHostName
upidInitHostName.description: the host name where the UPInit process runs

upiInitChildProcessEntry.name: upiInitChildProcessEntry
upiInitChildProcessEntry.description: the entry associated with each child process

upipInitIpAddr.name: upipInitIpAddr
upipInitIpAddr.description: the ip address of the host where UPInit runs

upipInitProcessType.name: upipInitProcessType
upipInitProcessType.description: the UPInit process type: UPAdmInit, UPLInit or UPApsInit

upipChildProcessType.name: upipChildProcessType
upipChildProcessType.description: the child process type, e.g. Dispatcher, Agent

upipChildProcessIpAddr.name: upipChildProcessIpAddr
upipChildProcessIpAddr.description: the ip address of the host where the child process runs

upipChildProcessHostName.name: upipChildProcessHostName
upipChildProcessHostName.description: the name of the host where the child process runs

upipChildProcessExePath.name: upipChildProcessExePath

upipChildProcessExeArgs.name: upipChildProcessExeArgs
upipChildProcessExeArgs.description: the arguments used when exeuting the child process

upipChildProcessState.name: upipChildProcessState
upipChildProcessState.description: the state of the child process

upipChildProcessStatus.name: upipChildProcessStatus
upipChildProcessStatus.description: how the child process is started

upiInitChildProcessStatsTable.name: upiInitChildProcessStatsTable
upiInitChildProcessStatsTable.description: the table holding child process statistics

upiInitChildProcessStatsEntry.name: upiInitChildProcessStatsEntry
upiInitChildProcessStatsEntry.description: the statistics associated with each child process type

upipsInitIpAddr.name: upipsInitIpAddr
upipsInitIpAddr.description: the ip address of the host where UPInit runs

upipsChildProcessType.name: upipsChildProcessType
upipsChildProcessType.description: the child process name, e.g. Dispatcher,Agent

upipsInitProcessType.name: upipsInitProcessType
upipsInitProcessType.description: the UPInit process name, e.g. UPLInit UPAdmInit

upipsChildProcessesStarted.name: upipsChildProcessesStarted
upipsChildProcessesStarted.description: the number of times processes of this type started

upipsChildProcessesDied.name: upipsChildProcessesDied
upipsChildProcessesDied.description: the number of times processes of this type died

upipsChildProcessesRunning.name: upipsChildProcessesRunning
upipsChildProcessesRunning.description: the number of times processes of this type running

upitTrapInfo.name: upitTrapInfo
upitTrapInfo.description: Text string which provides additional information about the trap.

upitChildProcessHostName.name: upitChildProcessHostName
upitChildProcessHostName.description: the hostname of the host where child process runs

upitChildProcessType.name: upitChildProcessType
upitChildProcessType.description: the child process type e.g. Dispatcher, Agent

upiChildProcessStart.name: upiChildProcessStart
upiChildProcessStart.description: An event that is generated when a child process is started/restarted.

upiChildProcessShutdown.name: upiChildProcessShutdown
upiChildProcessShutdown.description: An event that is generated when a child process is shut down. upitTrapInfo gives the condition.

upiInitFailToStart.name: upiInitFailToStart
upiInitFailToStart.description: An event that is generated when UPInit is failed to start itself.

upiInitShutdown.name: upiInitShutdown
upiInitShutdown.description: An event that is generated when UPInit is about to shutdown itself.

upiAllChildProcessesStop.name: upiAllChildProcessesStop
upiAllChildProcessesStop.description: An event that is generated when UPInit is about to stop all child processes.

upiAllChildProcessesRestart.name: upiAllChildProcessesRestart
upiAllChildProcessesRestart.description: An event that is generated when UPInit is about to restart all child process.

upiDatabaseConnectionDown.name: upiDatabaseConnectionDown
upiDatabaseConnectionDown.description: An event that is generated when UPInit detects that the database is down.

upiDatabaseConnectionUp.name: upiDatabaseConnectionUp
upiDatabaseConnectionUp.description: An event that is generated when UPInit detects that the database is back up.

upiChildProcessFailToStart.name: upiChildProcessFailToStart
upiChildProcessFailToStart.description: An event that is generated when a child process fails to start.

upiNoChildProcess.name: upiNoChildProcess
upiNoChildProcess.description: An event that is generated when no child process is started by this upiInit instance.

upiChildProcessesBelowMinimum.name: upiChildProcessesBelowMinimum
upiChildProcessesBelowMinimum.description: An event that is generated when the number of child processes started by means of TCP-Connect mechanism as defined in the cfg_init_tab becomes less than 2. This really applies to number of agents in most cases

upldHostName.name: upldHostName
upldHostName.description: Name of the host on which dispatcher resides.

upldPortNumber.name: upldPortNumber
upldPortNumber.description: Port number the dispatcher uses to listen for incomming airlink requests.

upldState.name: upldState
upldState.description: The state of the dispatcher: regular: routes airlink requests to UPLAgents; redirect: routes airlink requests to other UPLDispatchers permanently.

upldRequestsReceived.name: upldRequestsReceived
upldRequestsReceived.description: Requests that have been received since the dispatcher started.

upldRequestsDropped.name: upldRequestsDropped
upldRequestsDropped.description: Requests that have been dropped due to lack of resources since the dispatcher started.

upldUplAgentsLoaded.name: upldUplAgentsLoaded
upldUplAgentsLoaded.description: Total number of agents currently loaded in the dispatcher.

upldUplAgentsDisconnected.name: upldUplAgentsDisconnected
upldUplAgentsDisconnected.description: Total number of agents currently disconnected among all the agents loaded in the dispatcher.

upldSubscribersLoaded.name: upldSubscribersLoaded
upldSubscribersLoaded.description: Total number of subscribers currently loaded in the dispatcher.

upldKeyExchanges.name: upldKeyExchanges
upldKeyExchanges.description: Number of key exchanges since the dispatcher started.

upldTrapInfo.name: upldTrapInfo
upldTrapInfo.description: Text string which provides additional information about the trap.

upldUplAgentId.name: upldUplAgentId
upldUplAgentId.description: The UPLAgent identifier related to the trap.

upldStartup.name: upldStartup
upldStartup.description: An event that is generated when the dispatcher is started.

upldShutdown.name: upldShutdown
upldShutdown.description: An event that is generated when the dispatcher is shut down. upldTrapInfo gives the condition.

upldInvalidConfig.name: upldInvalidConfig
upldInvalidConfig.description: An event that is generated when the dispatcher detects an invalid configuration. upldTrapInfo gives the configuration name.

upldUplAgentConnectionDown.name: upldUplAgentConnectionDown
upldUplAgentConnectionDown.description: An event that is generated when the dispatcher detects that the connection to the UPLAgent is down. The UPLAgent is identified by upldAgentId. upldTrapInfo gives the host name where the UPLAgent resides.

upldDatabaseConnectionDown.name: upldDatabaseConnectionDown
upldDatabaseConnectionDown.description: An event that is generated when the dispatcher detects that the database is down.

upldOutOfResouce.name: upldOutOfResouce
upldOutOfResouce.description: An event that is generated when the dispatcher detects an out-of-resource condition. upldTrapInfo gives the resource name

upldUplAgentConnectionUp.name: upldUplAgentConnectionUp
upldUplAgentConnectionUp.description: An event that is generated when the dispatcher detects that the connection to the UPLAgent has come up. The UPLAgent is identified by upldAgentId. upldTrapInfo gives the host name where the UPLAgent resides.

upldDatabaseConnectionUp.name: upldDatabaseConnectionUp
upldDatabaseConnectionUp.description: An event that is generated when the dispatcher detects that the database has come into service.

uplAgentDescriptionTable.name: uplAgentDescriptionTable
uplAgentDescriptionTable.description: The table holding uplAgent identifying information.

uplAgentDescriptionEntry.description: The entry associated with each uplAgent.

uplaAgentIdentifier.name: uplaAgentIdentifier
uplaAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplaHostName.name: uplaHostName
uplaHostName.description: The host name of the uplAgent host.

uplaProcessId.name: uplaProcessId
uplaProcessId.description: The process id for the uplAgent.

uplaStartUpTime.name: uplaStartUpTime
uplaStartUpTime.description: The date and time the uplAgent started.

uplAgentWebAccessStatsTable.name: uplAgentWebAccessStatsTable
uplAgentWebAccessStatsTable.description: The table holding Web access statistics.

uplAgentWebAccessStatsEntry.name: uplAgentWebAccessStatsEntry
uplAgentWebAccessStatsEntry.description: The entry associated with each uplAgent.

uplawsAgentIdentifier.name: uplawsAgentIdentifier
uplawsAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplaHttpRequestsStarted.name: uplaHttpRequestsStarted
uplaHttpRequestsStarted.description: Number of http requests initiated since the uplAgent started.

uplaHttpRequestsSucceeded.name: uplaHttpRequestsSucceeded
uplaHttpRequestsSucceeded.description: Number of http requests that succeeded among all http requests initiated since the uplAgent started.

uplaHttpMeanResponseTime.name: uplaHttpMeanResponseTime
uplaHttpMeanResponseTime.description: Mean response time in milliseconds for http requests.

uplaHttpsRequestsStarted.name: uplaHttpsRequestsStarted
uplaHttpsRequestsStarted.description: Number of https requests initiated since the uplAgent started.

uplaHttpsRequestsSucceeded.name: uplaHttpsRequestsSucceeded
uplaHttpsRequestsSucceeded.description: Number of https requests that succeeded among all https requests initiated since the uplAgent started.

uplaHttpsMeanResponseTime.name: uplaHttpsMeanResponseTime
uplaHttpsMeanResponseTime.description: Mean response time in milliseconds for https requests.

uplAgentErrorStatsSummaryEntry.name: uplAgentErrorStatsSummaryEntry
uplAgentErrorStatsSummaryEntry.description: The entry associated with each uplAgent.

uplaesAgentIdentifier.name: uplaesAgentIdentifier
uplaesAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplaTotalErrors.name: uplaTotalErrors
uplaTotalErrors.description: Total number of errors that have occurred since the uplAgent started.

uplaSilentErrors.name: uplaSilentErrors
uplaSilentErrors.description: Number of error occurrences for the silent class of errors since the uplAgent started. The silent class of errors refers to errors caused by client requests, but for which the uplAgent does not send the errors back to the client.

uplaDeviceErrors.name: uplaDeviceErrors
uplaDeviceErrors.description: Number of error occurences for the device class of errors since the uplAgent started. The device class of errors refers to unregistered and unsupported devices.

uplaKeyErrors.name: uplaKeyErrors
uplaKeyErrors.description: Number of error occurrences for the key class of errors since the uplAgent started. The key class of errors refers to encryption key mismatch and unsupported encryption algorithms/configurations.

uplaSessionErrors.name: uplaSessionErrors
uplaSessionErrors.description: Number of error occurrences for the session class of errors since the uplAgent started. The session class of errors refers to invalid sessions.

uplaTransactionErrors.name: uplaTransactionErrors
uplaTransactionErrors.description: Number of error occurrences for the transaction class of errors since the uplAgent started. The transaction class of errors refers to all errors occurring while the transaction is conducted.

uplaOtherErrors.name: uplaOtherErrors
uplaOtherErrors.description: Number of error occurrences for all other errors since the uplAgent started. It is simply TotalErrors minus all the named class errors.

uplAgentErrorStatsDetailTable.name: uplAgentErrorStatsDetailTable
uplAgentErrorStatsDetailTable.description: The table holding detailed error statistics.

uplAgentErrorStatsDetailEntry.name: uplAgentErrorStatsDetailEntry
uplAgentErrorStatsDetailEntry.description: The entry associated with each error code in an uplAgent.

uplaedAgentIdentifier.name: uplaedAgentIdentifier
uplaedAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplaErrorCode.name: uplaErrorCode
uplaErrorCode.description: The error code as defined in uplAgent.

uplaErrorName.name: uplaErrorName
uplaErrorName.description: A text string describing the error name.

uplaErrorCount.name: uplaErrorCount
uplaErrorCount.description: Number of times the error has occurred since the uplAgent started.

uplAgentSessionStatsTable.name: uplAgentSessionStatsTable
uplAgentSessionStatsTable.description: The table holding uplAgent session statistics.

uplAgentSessionStatsEntry.name: uplAgentSessionStatsEntry
uplAgentSessionStatsEntry.description: The entry associated with each uplAgent.

uplassAgentIdentifier.name: uplassAgentIdentifier
uplassAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplaActiveSessions.name: uplaActiveSessions
uplaActiveSessions.description: Number of active sessions currently in the uplAgent.

uplaEncryptedSessions.name: uplaEncryptedSessions
uplaEncryptedSessions.description: Number of sessions that use encryption among all active sessions in the uplAgent.

uplaProtoSessions.name: uplaProtoSessions
uplaProtoSessions.description: Number of proto sessions that do not complete the session-creation procedure currently in the uplAgent.

uplaSessionsStarted.name: uplaSessionsStarted
uplaSessionsStarted.description: Number of sessions started since the uplAgent started.

uplaSessionsSucceeded.name: uplaSessionsSucceeded
uplaSessionsSucceeded.description: Number of sessions that have completed the session-creation procedure among all sessions started since the uplAgent started.

uplaKeyExchanges.name: uplaKeyExchanges
uplaKeyExchanges.description: Number of key exchanges that have completed since the uplAgent started.

uplAgentAirLinkStatsTable.name: uplAgentAirLinkStatsTable
uplAgentAirLinkStatsTable.description: The table holding uplAgent airlink traffic statistics.

uplAgentAirLinkStatsEntry.name: uplAgentAirLinkStatsEntry
uplAgentAirLinkStatsEntry.description: The entry associated with each uplAgent.

uplaasAgentIdentifier.name: uplaasAgentIdentifier
uplaasAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplaRequestsReceived.name: uplaRequestsReceived
uplaRequestsReceived.description: Number of requests that have been received by uplAgent since it started. Ack, Cancel, and SessComplete PDU's are not counted.

uplaRequestsDropped.name: uplaRequestsDropped
uplaRequestsDropped.description: Number of requests that have been dropped since the UPLagent started. Dropped requests include duplicated, invalid, and out of sequence PDU's.

uplaRequestsDuplicated.name: uplaRequestsDuplicated
uplaRequestsDuplicated.description: Number of duplicated requests that have been received since the uplAgent started.

uplaRequestsNotValid.name: uplaRequestsNotValid
uplaRequestsNotValid.description: Number of invalid requests that have been received since the uplAgent started.

uplaRepliesDelivered.name: uplaRepliesDelivered
uplaRepliesDelivered.description: Number of replies that have been successfully delivered to the browser client since the uplAgent started.

uplaRepliesTimedOut.name: uplaRepliesTimedOut
uplaRepliesTimedOut.description: Number of replies not delivered due to timeout since the uplAgent started.

uplAgentTransactionStatsTable.name: uplAgentTransactionStatsTable
uplAgentTransactionStatsTable.description: The table holding uplAgent transaction statistics.

uplAgentTransactionStatsEntry.name: uplAgentTransactionStatsEntry
uplAgentTransactionStatsEntry.description: The entry associated with each uplAgent.

uplatsAgentIdentifier.name: uplatsAgentIdentifier
uplatsAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplaTransactionsActive.name: uplaTransactionsActive
uplaTransactionsActive.description: Number of active transactions currently in the uplAgent.

uplaTransactionsStarted.name: uplaTransactionsStarted
uplaTransactionsStarted.description: Number of transactions that have started since the uplAgent started.

uplaTransactionsSucceeded.name: uplaTransactionsSucceeded
uplaTransactionsSucceeded.description: Number of transactions that have succeeded among all transactions started since the uplAgent started.

uplaMeanTransactionLife.name: uplaMeanTransactionLife
uplaMeanTransactionLife.description: Mean transaction lifetime measured in milliseconds.

uplaMeanResponseTime.name: uplaMeanResponseTime
uplaMeanResponseTime.description: Mean transaction response time in milliseconds,as measured from the browser's point of view.

uplaMeanRetriesPerThousandTxn.name: uplaMeanRetriesPerThousandTxn
uplaMeanRetriesPerThousandTxn.description: Number of retransmitted requests for every one thousand completed transactions.

uplAgentLimitedResourceTable.name: uplAgentLimitedResourceTable
uplAgentLimitedResourceTable.description: The table holding information about limited resource usage.

uplAgentWapWSPSessionStatsTable.description: The table holding uplAgent WAP session statistics.

uplAgentWapSessionStatsEntry.description: The entry associated with each uplAgent.

uplawssAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplAgentWapTransactionStatsEntry.description: The entry associated with each uplAgent.

uplawtsAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplAgentWapErrorStatsSummaryTable.description: The table holding WAP stack related error-summary statistics.

uplAgentWapErrorStatsSummaryEntry.name: uplAgentWapErrorStatsSummaryEntry
uplAgentWapErrorStatsSummaryEntry.description: The entry associated with each uplAgent.

uplawesAgentIdentifier.name: uplawesAgentIdentifier
uplawesAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplaTotalWapErrors.name: uplaTotalWapErrors
uplaTotalWapErrors.description: Total number of WAP stack errors that have occurred since the uplAgent started.

uplaOtherWapErrors.name: uplaOtherWapErrors
uplaOtherWapErrors.description: Number of error occurrences for all other errors since the uplAgent started. It is simply TotalErrors minus all the named class errors.

uplaSessionWapErrors.name: uplaSessionWapErrors
uplaSessionWapErrors.description: Number of error occurrences for the WAP session class of errors since the uplAgent started. The session class of errors refers to invalid sessions.

uplaTransactionWapErrors.name: uplaTransactionWapErrors
uplaTransactionWapErrors.description: Number of error occurrences for the WAP transaction class of errors since the uplAgent started. The transaction class of errors refers to all errors occurring while the transaction is conducted.

uplAgentWapErrorStatsDetailTable.name: uplAgentWapErrorStatsDetailTable
uplAgentWapErrorStatsDetailTable.description: The table holding detailed error statistics.

uplAgentWapErrorStatsDetailEntry.description: The entry associated with each error code in an uplAgent.

uplaweAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplaWapErrorCode.name: uplaWapErrorCode
uplaWapErrorCode.description: The error code as defined in uplAgent.

uplaWapErrorName.name: uplaWapErrorName
uplaWapErrorName.description: A text string describing the error name.

uplaWapErrorCount.name: uplaWapErrorCount
uplaWapErrorCount.description: Number of times the error has occurred since the uplAgent started.

uplasstAgentIdentifier.description: The unique identifier for each uplAgent.

uplAgentStackServiceLoaded.description: Has the Stack Service been loaded: (1) No (2) Yes.

uplAgentStackServiceAdaptorThreads.name: uplAgentStackServiceAdaptorThreads
uplAgentStackServiceAdaptorThreads.description: The number of Adaptor threads for this Stack Service.

uplAgentStackServiceWDPPortNumber.name: uplAgentStackServiceWDPPortNumber
uplAgentStackServiceWDPPortNumber.description: The WDP Port number for this Stack Service.

uplaTrapInfo.description: Text string that provides additional information about the trap.

uplaStartup.description: An event that is generated when the uplAgent is started.

uplaShutdown.description: An event that is generated when the uplAgent is shut down. uplaTrapInfo gives the reason for the shutdown.

uplaDatabaseConnectionDown.description: An event that is generated when the uplAgent detects that the database connection is down.

uplaFaxMgrConnectionDown.description: An event that is generated when the uplAgent detects that the fax manager is down.

uplaMessengerConnectionDown.description: An event that is generated when the uplAgent detects that the messenger is down.

uplaInvalidConfig.description: An event that is generated when the uplAgent detects an invalid configuration. uplaTrapInfo gives the configuration name.

uplaInternalFatalErrors.description: An event that is generated when the uplAgent detects an internal fatal error. uplaTrapInfo gives error name.

uplaOutOfResource.name: uplaOutOfResource
uplaOutOfResource.description: An event that is generated when the uplAgent detects reportable out-of-resource conditions. uplaTrapInfo gives the resource name.

uplNbRouterDescriptionEntry.description: The entry associated with each UPLNbRouter.

uplrNbRouterConnectionUp.name: uplrNbRouterConnectionUp
uplrNbRouterConnectionUp.description: An event that is generated by a client when the client detects the connection to an UPLNbRouter is back up.

uplrProtocolError.name: uplrProtocolError
uplrProtocolError.description: An event that is generated by a client process running narrowband airlink adaptor when it detects a protocol error in the messages exchange with the UPLNbRouter.
